description:
//Location
If you can get over the fact that this place is in the tenderloin it's a must visit! Also, during lunchtime or the day the area is bustling with people, so the location shouldn't deter you from this awesome spot! 

//Food
This sandwich was amazing, the bread was a little tough for being soft roll but the ingredients in this sandwich come together really well and some people prefer tougher breads. I got the pate and for people who are wondering what that is, it's similar to ground beef but mushier. Personally I tried it because it seemed unique but I'd probably go with a different meat since I didn't enjoy the consistency of the pate that much.

//Price-Service 
Often people get worried when they see a long line, but we came here at 12:30 on a Friday (peak lunchtime) and only had to wait fifteen minutes considering there was about 8 people in front of us waiting. The women making the sandwich and taking the order are quick and efficient as they seem to have been doing this for a long time. The real steal of this place is the fact that it's $4 dollars for their regular sandwiches and 4.50 for their combo, which has different meats in it. In SF price is always an issue but this spot is affordable and tasty, so I'll definitely be here again.
